[G]Cause I believe some good [C]cool clear spring [G]water
[D7]Will make this awful fever lose its [G]grip
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]I said momma there's good cold water in the [G]icebox
[D7]I fetched it up fresh late this [G]afternoon
[C]She said son now you be good and mind your [G]momma
[D7]Cause that water in the icebox just won't [G]do
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[C]So I ran down to the spring to fetch some [G]water
[C]She was crying as I softly shut the [D7]door
[G]And when I got back to [C]the house with good clear [G]water
[D7]My momma wasn't thirsty [G]any [D7]more
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[G]Through the years I've come [C]to understand and [G]value
[D7]The courage in my momma's gentle [G]soul
[C]And how she chose to bare her cross alone and spare [G]me
[D7]From watchin' the grim reaper take his [G]toll
{end_of_verse}

